Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
trPrintIgnoredPadNets(25.10)                      trPrintIgnoredPadNets(25.10)

Name
       trPrintIgnoredPadNets

Syntax
       trPrintIgnoredPadNets <value>

       Type: Integer

       Default: 0

       Sets  a  limit  to the number of nets to be printed during earlyGlobal-
       Route. This limit is used to warn about the nets that have connectivity
       from a pad term to a fterm without geometry. Without a geometry on  the
       terminal  these  nets  can  not be routed. A pad term is a pin of a pad
       logically connected to a top level module port (fterm).

       Type 'set trPrintIgnoredPadNets ' prior to earlyGlobalRoute to have  it
       report each net up to limit value.

       The default value of this integer variable is 0

Related Information
              * earlyGlobalRoute

